title: Hanover claims DI lead; Axtell holds off Cats
text: Hanover claims DI lead; Axtell holds off Cats Published: Thursday, October 8, 2015 10:29 PM CDT A 50-16 win Friday for Hanover put the Wildcats in the lead of District 4 in eight-man Division I, while district play just started last week for Division II.Axtell’s 30-24 win over visiting Frankfort to start district left the Eagles in third behind winners Pike Valley and Linn, according to points. Axtell has six points from its win against Frankfort. Pike Valley and Linn both have 21.But the standings will change after games Friday. Axtell is at Southern Cloud, Frankfort at Pike Valley and Hanover is home against Lincoln, Kan., for homecoming.Axtell 30, Frankfort 24A 1-yard touchdown by Axtell’s Kaleb Buessing with 8.1 seconds left in regulation earned the Eagles a district and Twin Valley League win against Frankfort. The Wildcats tied the game on an Adam Kenworthy 3-yard run with 1:19 to play. Kenworthy ran in the two-point conversion.It was Kenworthy who scored the first touchdown in the game on a 1-yard run with 5:30 to go in the first quarter. Jase Suther ran in the conversion. With 4:24 left in the quarter, Buessing hit Brice Koch on a 26-yard scoring pass. Buessing ran in the conversion for an 8-all game.Koch made a fumble recovery in the end zone to score with 4:05 to go in the second quarter. Buessing found Burke Deters on the two-point pass for a 16-8 lead.With 4:03 to go in the third quarter, Buessing scored on a 5-yard keeper and then hit Koch for the conversion pass and a 24-8 lead. Frankfort battled back. With 1:20 left in the third, Kenworthy scored on a 1-yard run and Suther ran in the conversion. The Wildcats tied the game at 24-all with Kenworthy’s 3-yard keeper late in the fourth.FHS 8 0 8 8 — 24AHS 8 8 8 6 — 30 F A
